Incident Response Runbook Flow. Five steps: 1) DETECT: Metrics/Alerts Trigger (Cost Spike, Error Rate, Quality Score). 2) TRIAGE: Provider vs System? All Users or Segment? 3) MITIGATE: Fallback Model, Clear Cache, Rollback Prompt. 4) RESOLVE: Root Cause, Fix Deploy, Enhanced Monitoring. 5) LEARN: Update Runbook, Sharpen Metrics, Post-Mortem. Circular flow with Hotline Escalation for Bias/Safety (bypass normal SLAs). German labels, incident response style.